    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Instead of framing it as \"messiness,\" you can formally discuss the impact of high within-group variance or measurement error. You might state that the observed effect size, while potentially large, was attenuated due to considerable residual error in the dataset. This indicates that the variability within the groups was high relative to the difference between the means, which reduced the statistical power of the test. This language shifts the focus from a failing result to a limitation of the data's precision.",
      "source": "target",
